qas.question: In what century was Eisenhower born?
Who was the oldest man to become President prior to Eisenhower?
How many times had Eisenhower been elected to office prior to becoming president?
What did Eisenhower have in common with presidents Taylor, Grant, Taft and Hoover?

answers.text: did not have prior elected office

context: Eisenhower was the last president born in the <a1_0>19th<a1_0/> century, and at age 62, was the oldest man elected President since <a2_0>James Buchanan<a2_0/> in 1856 (President Truman stood at <a0_0>64<a0_0/> in 1948 as the incumbent president at the time of his election four years earlier). Eisenhower was the only general to serve as President in the 20th century and the most recent President to have <a3_0>never<a3_0/> held elected office prior to the Presidency (The other Presidents who <a4_0>did not have prior elected office<a4_0/> were Zachary Taylor, Ulysses S. Grant, William Howard Taft and Herbert Hoover).
